PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778623866
OL,3,CRogue roofers laughed and joked about
OL,4,Cconning elderly out of thousands
OL,6,FThe rogue traders convinced homeowners
OL,7,Fin Dover, Canterbury, Ramsgate that
OL,8,Fchimney and roof repairs were needed,
OL,9,Fstarting with smaller quotes but then
OL,10,Finflated them into hundreds and
OL,11,Fsometimes thousands of pounds.
OL,13,FIn several cases 39 year old Cooper
OL,14,Feven escorted his victims to banks and
OL,15,Fcash machines if they tried to suggest
OL,16,Fthey didn't have the cash at home.
OL,18,FOne victim was advised by the
OL,19,Ffraudster to tell the bank that he was
OL,20,Fwithdrawing the money for Christmas
OL,21,Fpresents.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
